OL,3,CEnergy firms to offer 'zero standing
OL,4,Ccharge' tariffs under Ofgem plans
OL,6,FEnergy firms will have to offer
OL,7,Fhousehold tariffs free of standing
OL,8,Fcharges as an alternative to existing
OL,9,Fones under plans by regulator Ofgem.
OL,11,FThe regulator wants suppliers to have
OL,12,Fto offer "zero standing charge"
OL,13,Ftariffs alongside other tariffs by
OL,14,Fnext winter as part of plans to
OL,15,Faddress ballooning household energy
OL,16,Fdebt.
OL,18,FIt is also proposing new standards for
OL,19,Fsuppliers to make it easier for
OL,20,Fcustomers who are struggling to pay
OL,21,Ftheir bills to get support.
