OL,3,CEnergy firms to offer 'zero standing
OL,4,Ccharge' tariffs under Ofgem plans
OL,6,FStanding charges pay for the fixed
OL,7,Fcosts to suppliers of providing energy
OL,8,Fto homes.
OL,10,FSome suppliers already offer low or no
OL,11,Fstanding charge tariffs, which are at
OL,12,Fleast 10% below the price cap, but
OL,13,Fthey are not universal.
OL,15,FHowever, while these tariffs come with
OL,16,Fa lower standing charge, they do have
OL,17,Fa higher unit rate, and are therefore
OL,18,Fmore likely to benefit customers who
OL,19,Fuse less energy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/16
