OL,3,CEnergy firms to offer 'zero standing
OL,4,Ccharge' tariffs under Ofgem plans
OL,6,FOfgem said tens of thousands of
OL,7,Fconsumers responded to its call for
OL,8,Finput on standing charges, with many
OL,9,Fasking for them to be removed
OL,10,Faltogether, saying that this would
OL,11,Fmake it easier for them to manage
OL,12,Ftheir bills or pay back debt.
OL,14,FHowever, those who were high users of
OL,15,Fenergy, often for medical and health
OL,16,Freasons, would see their bills rise
OL,17,Fsignificantly, meaning it was
OL,18,Fimportant for households to retain a
OL,19,Fchoice of tariff.
