OL,6,FIt also warned that the level of debt
OL,7,Fbuilt up during the energy crisis had
OL,8,Fbecome "unsustainable", saying it
OL,9,Frequired a "bespoke, one-off solution
OL,10,Fto tackle it that will drive down the
OL,11,Fcosts of debt in the long term for the
OL,12,Fbenefit of all consumers".
OL,14,FEnergy debt and arrears have continued
OL,15,Fto grow, reaching #3.82 billion in
OL,16,FSeptember ` a 91% or #1.82 billion
OL,17,Fincrease in two years.
