OL,3,CEnergy firms to offer 'zero standing
OL,4,Ccharge' tariffs under Ofgem plans
OL,6,FTim Jarvis, director general of
OL,7,Fmarkets at Ofgem, said: "We know that
OL,8,Fmany households continue to struggle
OL,9,Fwith bills after the events of the
OL,10,Fenergy crisis, which is why earlier
OL,11,Fthis year, we took steps to consider
OL,12,Fall the issues around affordability
OL,13,Fand debt ` including the impact of the
OL,14,Fstanding charge.
OL,16,F"Today we're setting out the next
OL,17,Fsteps in what Ofgem can do to meet
OL,18,Fthese challenges, as part of our work
OL,19,Fto make sure the energy market is
OL,20,Fworking in consumers' interests.
OL,26,@oD@YOUxD@AOU
