OL,6,FRichard Neudegg, director of
OL,7,Fregulation at Uswitch.com, said: "The
OL,8,Fpromise of more zero or low standing
OL,9,Fcharge tariffs options by next winter
OL,10,Fcould help bring more choice to the
OL,11,Fmarket, and might be a good choice for
OL,12,Fsome lower consumption households.
OL,14,F"But consumers must beware that the
OL,15,Ftrade-off for lower standing charges
OL,16,Fwill be higher unit rates, so
